Below is a JavaScript function that uses Regular Expressions to extract a three character code like "1Jn" from a filename in the format "57-1Jn.usfm". 

```javascript
function extractCode(filename) {
    // Define regex pattern for the desired format
    const regex = /(\d+)-([A-Za-z0-9]{3})\.usfm$/;

    // Use match method to find matches
    const matches = filename.match(regex);

    // If there's a match, return the second captured group (the 3 character code)
    if (matches && matches.length >= 2) {
        return matches[2];
    } else {
        return null;
    }
}
```

You can use this function by passing in a filename string like so:

```javascript
const filename = "57-1Jn.usfm";
const code = extractCode(filename);
console.log(code); // Outputs: 1Jn
```
